cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY

The paper presents a new evolutionary algorithm for optimization problems, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of probability distributions and diversity preservation, which are topics related to machine learning and statistics, respectively. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed algorithm to antenna array synthesis, which could be considered as a control systems problem, and hence, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category.
